y floured hands, roll each piece into a sausage shape (Ø 2 cm). Cut sausages into pieces 1 cm long to form dumplings. Press lightly on gnocchi with a floured fork, removing gnocchi from work surface gently with a spatula if necessary. Brush off excess flour from gnocchi then transfer to a baking tray, cover loosely with cling film and set aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl."},{"content":"Place remaining 30 g flour, butter, milk, Taleggio and remaining 1 tsp salt  in mixing bowl then cook <b>8 min\/90°C\/speed 4<b>. Meanwhile, bring a large pan of water, with 1 tsp salt added,  to a boil and cook gnocchi, in batches, until they rise to the surface. Remove and drain gnocchi with a slotted spoon then transfer to a serving bowl."},{"content":"Pour Taleggio cheese sauce over gnocchi and sprinkle with chives to serve."}],"hintsAndTricks":["Freeze any leftover, uncooked gnocchi (without sauce). Arrange pieces on a tray and put them in the freezer for 30 minutes until firm, then transfer to a freezer-proof bag. They can be cooked straight from frozen, with a few extra minutes added to the cooking time.<br>","To taste, sprinkle with grated Parmigiano Reggiano."],"basicInfo":["medium","45m","1h 40m","6 portions"]}